Compile the program with the command: "make"

Lorenz parameters have default values but can be modified with the command line options: -s, -b, -r
Each option must be followed with a value for the parameter modification to occur

An example command to run the program: "./hw2 -s 15 -r 23.4"

The view can be rotated using the arrow keys

Much of this program was built from the foundation of ex4.c